---
import DefaultLayout from '../../layouts/DefaultLayout.astro'
import { Card, Pagination } from 'accessible-astro-components'

export async function getStaticPaths({ paginate }) {
  const newdata = [{
    "userId": "Dipanjan Rout",
    "id": 1,
    "imgsrc": "/market.jpg",
    "title": "Discover the Top 5 D2C Trends Shaping 2023's E-Commerce Landscape",
    "body": "As online shopping becomes the norm, Direct-to-Consumer (D2C) brands are taking center stage in revolutionizing retail dynamics. The year ahead, 2023, promises an exhilarating journey for these enterprises as fresh trends emerge and established ones evolve. With the D2C sector's impressive growth trajectory and the influence of technology, evolving consumer behaviors, and ongoing global dynamics, staying in sync with these trends is paramount for businesses aiming to flourish in this dynamic setting.",
    "points": [{"head": "1. Personalization: Elevating Customer Experiences", 
                "para": "In a fusion of data and technology, D2C brands are scaling new heights of personalization. By adeptly gathering and analyzing consumer preferences, behaviors, and trends, brands now tailor products and marketing endeavors with precision. The employment of advanced tools such as AI and machine learning enables crafting one-of-a-kind experiences for every customer, nurturing robust connections. This strategic alignment not only addresses individual needs but also elevates overall customer contentment.",},
                {"head": "2. Subscription Models: Fostering Loyalty and Sustainable Revenue Streams", 
                "para": "The ascent of subscription-based models is reshaping D2C brands' engagement tactics. Through enticing monthly subscriptions or product replenishment services, brands secure steady streams of revenue while nurturing client loyalty. Beyond the convenience for consumers, these models power customer retention, consequently bolstering the lifetime value of each patron.",},
                {"head": "3. Sustainability as a Defining Factor", 
                "para": "In a crowded marketplace, today's consumers wield the power to choose brands resonating with their values. Sustainability has emerged as a pivotal factor, particularly among environmentally conscious Gen-Z shoppers. D2C brands, especially those directly connecting with consumers, can no longer afford to disregard the sustainability mandate. Embracing eco-friendly practices not only forges deeper customer connections but also sets brands apart in the fiercely competitive market.",},
                {"head": "4. Livestream Shopping: Immersive and Enlightening", 
                "para": "The digital age has overhauled how consumers access information. Livestream shopping, which originated on platforms like YouTube and subsequently migrated to TikTok and Instagram, is revolutionizing product reviews. These video-driven formats deliver intricate insights, spanning try-ons to durability tests, in a riveting manner. Collaborations with influencers for live reviews empower brands to tap into their extensive reach and garner the trust of followers seeking authentic endorsements.",},
                {"head": "5. Social Commerce Integration: Expanding Brand Influence", 
                "para": "The seamless amalgamation of e-commerce within social media platforms remains a strategic forte for D2C brands. Partnering with influencers amplifies brand visibility and directly connects with potential customers who value authentic endorsements. Picking the right influencer and platform aligns with the brand's objectives, optimizing the impact of influencer synergies.",},],
  },
  {
    "userId": "Dipanjan Rout",
    "id": 2,
    "imgsrc": "/seo.jpg",
    "title": "Exploring the Leading 7 Scaling Hurdles Confronting D2C Brands in 2023",
    "body": "Amid the ongoing transformation of India's retail realm by the digital revolution, Direct-to-Consumer (D2C) brands are prospering within an ecosystem energized by over 700 million internet users and 190 million online shoppers. The allure of establishing direct connections with consumers, bypassing traditional intermediaries, has driven a surge in D2C brands. With a remarkable 600+ brands already in operation and a market size estimated around $55 billion USD in 2022, the terrain is undeniably dynamic, yet it's replete with challenges that require ingenious solutions.",
    "points": [{"head": "1. Balancing Personalized Touch and Acquisition Costs",
                "para": "Juggling a personalized customer experience while expanding can prove to be a formidable task. Utilizing the capabilities of AI and data analytics, brands are harnessing technology to provide tailored interactions on a grand scale. However, delicately treading the line between automation and authenticity is pivotal. Sustaining the brand's human essence amid growth demands a nuanced equilibrium. Furthermore, the escalating costs of customer acquisition pose a challenge that mandates adaptive strategies and a robust, agile team.",},
                {"head": "2. Mastering the Supply Chain Maze Efficiently",
                "para": "Efficient management of the supply chain stands as a pivotal pillar for seamless scaling. From streamlining order processing to ensuring timely deliveries, D2C brands grapple with complexities, especially in cross-border shipping contexts. Collaborating closely with shipping partners, carriers, and staying abreast of customs policies becomes imperative for efficient inventory management and ensuring customer contentment.",},
                {"head": "3. Expanding Market Presence With Prudent Acquisition Expenditure",
                "para": "The predicament of broadening market presence while judiciously managing acquisition expenditures is a perplexity encountered by numerous D2C brands. An astute approach involves pinpointing high-value segments, enabling brands to weather the escalation in acquisition costs as they secure niche markets. Striking a balance between ambitious growth pursuits and budgetary confines necessitates precision and astute foresight.",},
                {"head": "4. Navigating the Personalization Paradox",
                "para": "The Personalization Paradox arises from the craving for personalized experiences juxtaposed with escalating privacy apprehensions. Brands shoulder the responsibility of upholding relevance, engagement, and privacy compliance simultaneously. This intricate tightrope walk necessitates innovative strategies that embrace consumer preferences while respecting their data privacy.",},
                {"head": "5. Assembling the Ideal Team for Scaling",
                "para": "The success of scaling D2C marketing initiatives hinges on assembling a proficient team adept at crafting compelling messages, orchestrating campaigns across diverse channels, and comprehending the intricacies of digital marketing. Although the talent pool is rich, identifying individuals endowed with the precise blend of expertise can be a time-intensive challenge, often leading to time losses in growth strategies.",},
                {"head": "6. Striking Equilibrium Between Outreach and Engagement*",
                "para": "The pursuit of achieving the perfect harmony between broad outreach and profound engagement signifies a pivotal scaling obstacle. While casting a wide net to capture a substantial audience is enticing, it's engagement and action that fuel triumph. In the realm of D2C marketing, quality prevails over quantity. Placing emphasis on meaningful connections over superficial impressions yields more fruitful results, even when resources are restricted.",},
                {"head": "7. Pivoting to Omnichannel Amid Evolving Constraints",
                "para": "Confronted with data constraints and escalating competition, D2C brands are compelled to pivot toward an omnichannel strategy. Collaborative ventures with retail partners can proffer the extended timeline imperative for D2C initiatives to yield profitability. This strategic shift empowers brands to leverage a broader platform while aligning with the ever-evolving dynamics of the market.",}]
  },
  ]

  return paginate(newdata, { pageSize: 6 })
}

const { page } = Astro.props
---

<DefaultLayout
  title="Blog"
>
  <section class="my-12">
    <div class="space-content container">
      <h1>Blogs</h1>
      <p class="text-2xl">
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="my-12">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="text-sm"><em>Post {page.start + 1} through {page.end + 1} of {page.total} total posts</em></p>
      <ul class="my-3">
        {
          page.data.map((post) => (
            <li>
              <Card
                img={post.imgsrc}
                url={'/blog/' + post.title.replaceAll(' ', '-').toLowerCase()}
                title={post.title}
                footer={'Writer: ' + post.userId}
              >
                <span class="line-clamp-3">{post.body}</span>
              </Card>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
      <div class="mt-12 grid place-content-center">
        <Pagination
          firstPage={page.url.prev ? '/blog' : null}
          previousPage={page.url.prev ? page.url.prev : null}
          nextPage={page.url.next ? page.url.next : null}
          lastPage={page.url.next ? `/blog/${Math.round(page.total / page.size)}` : null}
          currentPage={page.currentPage}
          totalPages={Math.round(page.total / page.size)}
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</DefaultLayout>

<style lang="scss">
  ul {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    grid-gap: 4rem;

    @media (min-width: 550px) {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      grid-gap: 2rem;
    }

    @media (min-width: 950px) {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
  }
</style>
